column5: had another great weekend...  managed 95 walleye on saturday... in about 8 hours... most were small fish on the jig but 10 were 20-24 inches on the troll at dark...  then with the nasty weather on sunday i only got out for the evening bite... managed 9 walleye from 20-24 inches and a tiny little musky in about 2-3 hours...  no pics cause they were small....  but next time out im gunna keep a couple for a fish fry so ill get some pics of these goofy looking fat fat walleye... they are literally like footballs...
hahahaha.  I'm laughing because I caught one walleye in 8 hours of fishing.  YOU SUCK MIKE.

lol  hey... this is new to me also... i figured out this pattern this fall and its a blast....  loads of walleye in huge schools... but they are very small... or  at least smaller then im used to... 18 inches and under...  then in the evening i can usually manage to troll up about 10 nicer size eyes...  makes for a really fun day
Awesome Mike !!! You know something, Rod Caster and I are gonna have to book a day with you. What d'ya Think RC?
That would make for a good roadtrip with my gf next summer.   I'll put this idea in my backpocket.
I'm not asking for specifics, but what area are you fishing? I'm guessing NW Ontario
congrats, you have caught more walleye in 8 hours then I have in my lifetime
